== Potato, Pepper, Onion & Cilantro Hash ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil (2 sheets for 4). Wash
and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice
@long green pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @red onion{1};
cut one half into ½-inch-thick wedges (whole onion for 4). Zest and quarter
@lime{1}. Mice @cilantro{¼%ounce}.

Toss potatoes, green pepper, and onion wedges on prepared #sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top
rack for ~{5%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season
all over with salt, then rub with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp} to
coat.

After veggies have roasted 5 minutes, carefully add chicken to same sheet.
Return to top rack until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 4 servings,
divide veggies and chicken between prepared sheets; roast veggies on top rack
and chicken on middle rack.)

> Grilling Alternative: Skip adding chicken to sheet with veggies. You'll grill
it in the next step!

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp},
@Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @chipotle powder{1%tsp} (be sure to measure—we sent
more), and a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Once chicken and veggies are cooked through, remove sheet from oven. Spoon
half the chipotle BBQ sauce (save the rest for serving) over chicken.

Return to top rack until glaze is tacky, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Grilling Alternative: Heat a well-oiled #grill{} or #grill pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through
(we suggest 3-5 minutes per side, but grills can vary). In the last 1-2
minutes of cooking, brush both sides with half the chipotle BBQ sauce
(save the rest for serving).

== To Serve ==

Toss veggies with lime zest and half the cilantro. Thinly slice chicken
crosswise.

Divide veggie hash between plates and top with chicken. Sprinkle with
remaining cilantro. Drizzle with remaining chipotle BBQ sauce (or serve on
the side). Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.